Package smtools.exceptions

Provides various classes for exception handling.

See:
          Description

Exception Summary
DateTimeFormatException Indicates a malformed Date or TimeStamp object.
FileCantBeCreatedException Indicates that an attempt to create a file denoted by the specified filename has failed.
FileDoesNotExistException Indicates that an attempt to open the file denoted by the specified filename has failed.
FileParseException Indicates that an attempt to parse a line in the file denoted by the specified filename has failed.
FileReadException Indicates that an attempt to read from the file denoted by the specified filename has failed.
FileWriteException Indicates that an attempt to write a value to the file denoted by the specified filename has failed.
RegistryException Indicates an error involving the Registry.
SoundPlayingException Indicates that playing of a sound has failed.
 

Package smtools.exceptions Description

Provides various classes for exception handling.

This package encapsulates all the exceptions that occur in the SMTools classes.
